28/12/2007
THE HAGUE, The Netherlands -- Defence witnesses are expected to begin testifying on behalf of former Macedonian Interior Minister Ljube Boskovski on January 29th, his lawyer, Edina Rasidovic, told a news conference Thursday (December 27th). 
She added that the defence plans to call only five witnesses and one forensic expert, compared to the 57 witnesses called by prosecutors at The Hague.
Boskovski and former senior Macedonian security official Johan Tarculovski are charged with war crimes committed against ethnic Albanians during a two-day raid on the village of Ljuboten in August 2001. 
(Dnevnik, Utrinski Vesnik - 28/12/07; MIA, A1 TV, Focus - 27/12/07)
